<h3>User Stories</h3>
	<ol>
		<li class="complete">As a user, I want to be able to see a list of beer styles.</li>
		<li class="complete">As a user, I want to be able to add a beer and it's related data to the website.</li>
		<li class="complete">As a user, I want to have my own account.</li>
		<li class="complete">As a user, I want to be able to log in using my email address or my username.</li>
		<li class="complete">As a user, I want to have my own profile page.</li>
		<li class="complete">As a user, I want my profile to have an easy-to-remember URL.</li>
			<ul>
				<li class="complete">fermently.com/username</li>
			</uL>
		<li class="complete">As a user, I want to connect beers to my profile.</li>
		<li class="complete">As a user, I want to see a list of beers that I've brewed, in descending chronological order (<%= link_to "ActiveRecord Ordering", "http://guides.rubyonrails.org/active_record_querying.html#ordering" %>).</li>
		<li class="complete">As a user, I want to be able to search all beers added to the system (<%= link_to "RailsCast", "http://railscasts.com/episodes/37-simple-search-form" %>).</li>
		<li class="complete">As a user, I want to be able to see my friends profile pages.</li>
		<li class="complete">As a user, I want to be able to to be followed by my friends, and to be able to follow them (<%= link_to "StackOverflow", "http://stackoverflow.com/questions/3397920/relationship-like-twitter-followers-followed-in-activerecord" %>).</li>
		<li class="complete">As a user, I want to add a brewer that I'm following to a beer that I brewed (<%= link_to "M:N relationship RailsCast", "http://railscasts.com/episodes/47-two-many-to-many" %>).</li>
		<li class="complete">As a user, I want to be able to block someone from following me.</li>
		<li class="complete">As a user, I want to be able to unblock someone.</li>
		<li class="complete">As a user, I want to be able to stop following someone (<%= link_to "concept article [I wound up using a more streamlined version of this]", "http://ryantownsend.co.uk/post/13058102942/unobtrusive-object-deletion-in-rails" %>).</li>
		<li class="complete">As a user, I want to be able to see averages of metrics for specific beers listed on it's beer style page (<%= link_to "ActiveRecord.average()", "http://api.rubyonrails.org/classes/ActiveRecord/Calculations.html#method-i-average" %>, <%= link_to "avg from an Array", "http://stackoverflow.com/questions/1341271/how-do-i-create-an-average-from-a-ruby-array" %>).</li>
		<li class="complete">As a user, I want to see a list of beer styles from BreweryDB.(<%= link_to "db:seed RailsCast", "http://railscasts.com/episodes/179-seed-data" %>, <%= link_to "breweryDB", "http://www.brewerydb.com/" %>)</li>
		<li class="complete">As a user, I want to be able to search for users (<%= link_to "acts_as_indexed", "https://github.com/dougal/acts_as_indexed" %>).</li>
		<li class="complete">As a user, I want to be able to search for beer styles (<%= link_to "acts_as_indexed", "https://github.com/dougal/acts_as_indexed" %>).</li>
		<li class="complete">As a user, I want dates on the website to be more readable (<%= link_to "apiDock article", "http://apidock.com/ruby/DateTime/strftime" %>).</li>
		<li>As a user, I want to have a 'dashboard' or landing page for when I log in. Something showing the following:</li>
			<ul>
				<li>Recently brewed beers from my friends</li>
				<li class="complete">New accounts</li>
				<li>New Happenings on the site (did my friends follow someone?)</li>
				<li>Beer Style of the week</li>
			</ul>
		<li><i>As a user, I want to be able to share my beer over facebook (<%= link_to "developers.facebook.com", "https://developers.facebook.com/docs/plugins/share-button/" %>).</i></li>
		<li><i>As a user, I want to be able to share my beer over twitter (<%= link_to "about.twitter.com", "https://about.twitter.com/resources/buttons#tweet" %>).</i></li>
		<li>As an admin, I want to be able to confirm user identity through Twitter (<%= link_to "omniauth RailsCast", "http://asciicasts.com/episodes/241-simple-omniauth" %>, <%= link_to "omniauth-twitter", "https://github.com/arunagw/omniauth-twitter" %>), facebook (<%= link_to "omniauth-facebook", "https://github.com/plataformatec/devise/wiki/OmniAuth%3A-Overview" %>), or email (<%= link_to "StackOverflow", "http://stackoverflow.com/questions/8186584/how-do-i-set-up-email-confirmation-with-devise" %>).</li> 
		<li><i>As a user, I want all tables to be sortable by column (<%= link_to "railsCast", "http://railscasts.com/episodes/228-sortable-table-columns" %>)</i></li>
		<li><i>As a user, I want to see a website that looks like it's from the year 2014 (<%= link_to "getBootstrap", "http://getbootstrap.com/" %>).</i></li>
		<li></li>
		<li>As a user, I want to be able eat bacon and bagels with cream cheese.</li>
		<li>As a user, I only want myself and fellow brewers to be able to edit/destroy a beer. (CanCan)</li>
		<li>As a user, I want to be able to view a category of beer styles.</li>
		<li>As a user, I want to be able to add a profile picture! (omniauth-facebook)(Paperclip)</li>
		<li>As a user, I want to be able to add a picture to my beer. (Paperclip)</li>
		<li>As a user, I want to be able to list my homebrews on Untappd (<%= link_to "Untappd API", "https://untappd.com/api/docs" %>).</li>
		<li>As a user, I want to receive reminders about my beers (<%= link_to "Action Mailer basics -- guides.rubyonrails.org", "http://guides.rubyonrails.org/action_mailer_basics.html" %>, <%= link_to "simple RailsCast", "http://railscasts.com/episodes/61-sending-email" %>).</li>
		<li>As a developer, I would like to explore streamlined follow/follower system using the <%= link_to "acts_as_follower", "https://github.com/tcocca/acts_as_follower" %> gem.</li>
	</ol>

